cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for hashing, which is commonly used in computer vision and information retrieval applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on the learning process and optimization of the deep networks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on real-world datasets, which indicates that it may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
